<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{7}{y}={75}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{3}{y}=-{90}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+-{7}{y}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={75}-{\left(-{7}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{75}-{\left(-{7}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{{75}-{\left(-{7}{y}\right)}}}{{6}}\right)}+{3}{y}=-{90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{6}}\cdot{\left({75}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{6}}{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{112.5}-{\left(-{10.5}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10.5}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}=-{90}--{112.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10.5}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}={22.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{10.5}+{\left({3}\right)}\right)}{y}={22.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7.5}{y}={22.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{22.5}}{{-{{7.5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+-{7}{\left(-{3}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}+{\left({21}\right)}={75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={75}-{\left({21}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}={54}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{54}}{{6}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

